# Let's create check_solution.py from AtCoder typical solution tester; but the user said it's provided.
# We'll create a simple tester that runs sample inputs and checks outputs.
sample_inputs = ["21\n","998244353\n","264428617\n"]
sample_outputs = ["1\n","0\n","32\n"]
import subprocess, sys, textwrap
for inp, expected in zip(sample_inputs, sample_outputs):
    p = subprocess.Popen(["python","solution.py"], stdin=subprocess.PIPE, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE, text=True)
    out,err = p.communicate(inp)
    print('Input:', inp.strip())
    print('Expected:', expected.strip())
    print('Got:', out.strip())
    if out.strip()==expected.strip():
        print('PASS')
    else:
        print('FAIL')
    if err:
        print('Stderr:', err)
    print('---')
